instanceof check if the object in the heap is an instance of that type, 
not whether if the reference is that type

EX: tiven the above class definiton, which of these statements MUST be 
TRUE so that the following cast operation executes without errors
Child c = (Child)p;

CORRECT ANSWER: p instanceof child

True or False? When a class implements an interface, it MUST override all 
the abstract methods defined in that interface.
TRUE


if two object types are not directly related, use explicit casting:

